column2: I am not using Percipio (signed up through my company's training portal).  Are there materials needed?
column5:
Percipio users can access documents including the session slides, attendance tracker document, etc by followng these steps.

Step 1. Log into Percipio
Step 2. Select Library > Showcase > Skillsoft Bootcamps
Step 3. Choose Project Management Bootcamps
Step 4. Select the Project Management Professional (PMP) ATP Bootcamp: 5 Day Cohort channel
Step 5. Select the Resources tab to the right of the Attend tab in the Bootcamp channel. Download the 5 Class Slides

Non-Percipio and Percipio users can access documents including the session slides and attendance tracker from GitHub.

https://github.com/Skillsoft-Content/PMP5Day

Step 1. Log into Percipio
Step 2. Select Library > Showcase > Skillsoft Bootcamps
Step 3. Choose Project Management Bootcamps
Step 4. Select the Project Management Professional (PMP) ATP Bootcamp: 5 Day Cohort channel
Step 5. Select the Resources tab to the right of the Attend tab in the Bootcamp channel. Download the 5 Class Slides

Non-Percipio and Percipio users can access documents including the session slides and attendance tracker from GitHub.

column2: is there is a possiility of replay of the sessions?
column5: is there is a possiility of replay of the sessions?

column2: is there is a possiility of replay of the sessions?
column5:
Yes, all attendees will be provided access to the recordings. After a session is presented live, you can send a request to mentoring@skillsoft.com and we will give you a direct link to access the recording that is password protected or you can wait for the next session, and we can provide it for you then.

Please note that to get credit for the bootcamp, you must attend the sessions live.

With that in mind, you can replace one live session with a recording and still qualify for the certificate of completion at the end of the bootcamp. If you miss more than one live session, you will need to attend the equivalent session in a future 5-Day Cohort. Please note that any session where you miss more than 15 minutes is considered a missed session.

column2: I am a Percipio user and went to Percipio Journey page but cannot find the Attendance Tracker.  How do I log my attendance?
column5:
Open a new tab in your browser, and then follow the steps to find resources and then follow these steps.

Step 1. Log into Percipio
Step 2. Select Library > Showcase > Skillsoft Bootcamps
Step 3. Choose Project Management Bootcamps
Step 4. Select the Project Management Professional (PMP) ATP Bootcamp: 5 Day Cohort channel
Step 5. Select the Resources tab to the right of the Attend tab in the Bootcamp channel. Download the 5 Class Slides

Non-Percipio and Percipio users can access documents including the session slides and attendance tracker from GitHub.

https://github.com/Skillsoft-Content/PMP5Day

Click Code and then Download Zip to get all resources from GitHub.

column2: I am on percipio, is there manual action required for attendance apart from attending live or complete replay such as filling any timesheets ?
column5: Percipio is now able to track your attendance in a session automatically; however, we still recommend that you use the attendance tracking document to track any logins and logouts to the session to ensure you are aware if you miss more than 15 minutes in a session, as that is considered a missed session.  in addition, you can upload your tracking document during the certificate of compeltion request process.

column2: do I need to upload the attendance doc somewhere
column5:
Please review the documentation in your Bootcamp rsources.

Open a new tab in your browser, and then follow the steps to find resources and then follow these steps.

Step 1. Log into Percipio
Step 2. Select Library > Showcase > Skillsoft Bootcamps
Step 3. Choose Project Management Bootcamps
Step 4. Select the Project Management Professional (PMP) ATP Bootcamp: 5 Day Cohort channel
Step 5. Select the Resources tab to the right of the Attend tab in the Bootcamp channel. Download the 5 Class Slides

Non-Percipio and Percipio users can access documents including the session slides and attendance tracker from GitHub.

https://github.com/Skillsoft-Content/PMP5Day

Click Code and then Download Zip to get all resources from GitHub.

column2: Do we need to purchase the learner Kit in percipio?
column5: Do we need to purchase the learner Kit in percipio?

column2: Do we need to purchase the learner Kit in percipio?
column5:
The Learner Kit is not available in Percipio. You would only need the Learner Kit if you plan to use this training to meet the 35 contact hours of project management education on your PMP application.

Your organization’s training coordinator or HR Department should be helping to facilitate the purchase of the learner kit by contacting your company's Skillsoft Account Executive who will provide them with your access key. If your company doesn’t know whom their Skillsoft Account Executive is to help facilitate the purchase of the Learner Kit they can contact our Customer Support Team.

https://support.skillsoft.com/contact.asp

If there is no process setup for them and they are asking you to purchase it on your own, you can start the purchase of the Learning kit from this website by clicking on the Buy button.  You will be redirected to another page to make the purchase.

https://www.skillsoft.com/pmp-voucher-offering

column2: Precipio - my library just says practice and attend - no watch or read is showing up
column5:
You will need to navigate to the Project Management Professional (PMP) ATP Bootcamp: 5 Day Cohort channel in Percipio. To quickly locate this channel, search for ‘Project Management Professional (PMP) ATP Bootcamp: 5 Day Cohort’ in the search field on your training site. On the channel page, you should see a Resources drop-down menu on the right side of the screen. Alternatively, you can get resources from our GitHub site.

GitHub URL:
https://github.com/Skillsoft-Content/PMP5Day

If you are in the proper channel in Percipio and you are not seeing the Watch and Read tabs, please contact your organization's training coordinator for assistance or our Customer Support team.  You may contact Customer Support by email at support@Skillsoft.com, or for immediate assistance, they are available by telephone and chat. The telephone numbers based on geographical areas and chat option can be found online at http://support.Skillsoft.com/contact.asp

column5: percipio user, what is the learner kit for?

column2: percipio user, what is the learner kit for?
column5:
The Learner Kit is required if you plan to use this bootcamp to meet the 35 contact hours of project management education for your PMP application. The Learner Kit includes the following items.

Student Manual
Project Manager Checklists
Student Resources
Post Class Survey
Spotlight Videos
Self-Knowledge Check
And some other items

column5:
To purchase it on your own, you can start the purchase of the Learning kit from this website by clicking on the Buy button.  You will be redirected to another page to make the purchase.

https://www.skillsoft.com/pmp-voucher-offering

The e-commerce price is $119, reflecting PMI’s pricing for the content and the additional e-commerce processing charges and tax. It may take a few days to receive the email with the access key with instructions on how to claim your Learner Kit.

Note 1: The e-commerce price is subject to change.

Note 2: The access key will be emailed to you from donotreply@imarc.com. Please be sure to check your Junk or Spam folders. If you don't receive the email with your access key after a few days please contact Customer Support.

https://support.skillsoft.com/contact.asp

Access Keys must be redeemed within 12 months of purchase. Once redeemed, your materials are available for 12 months. Access Keys can only be redeemed once.

column5:
Please read the attendance documentation and video in your resources. Open a new tab in your browser first, and then follow the steps to find resources and then follow these steps.

Step 1. Log into Percipio
Step 2. Select Library > Showcase > Skillsoft Bootcamps
Step 3. Choose Project Management Bootcamps
Step 4. Select the Project Management Professional (PMP) ATP Bootcamp: 5 Day Cohort channel
Step 5. Select the Resources tab to the right of the Attend tab in the Bootcamp channel. Download the 5 Class Slides

Non-Percipio and Percipio users can access documents including the session slides and attendance tracker from GitHub.

https://github.com/Skillsoft-Content/PMP5Day

To purchase it on your own, you can start the purchase of the Learning kit from this website by clicking on the Buy button.  You will be redirected to another page to make the purchase.

https://www.skillsoft.com/pmp-voucher-offering

The e-commerce price is $119, reflecting PMI’s pricing for the content and the additional e-commerce processing charges and tax. It may take a few days to receive the email with the access key with instructions on how to claim your Learner Kit.

Note 1: The e-commerce price is subject to change.

Note 2: The access key will be emailed to you from donotreply@imarc.com. Please be sure to check your Junk or Spam folders. If you don't receive the email with your access key after a few days please contact Customer Support.

https://support.skillsoft.com/contact.asp

Access Keys must be redeemed within 12 months of purchase. Once redeemed, your materials are available for 12 months. Access Keys can only be redeemed once.

column2: Percipio Student - How is leading project in the Military for over ten years count?
column5:
The Mentoring Team does not review PMI Test Candidates resume work experience or the work experience documented on their application to determine if their experience qualifies. PMI application reviewers will determine if your experience qualifies.

That being said, here are a few important things to keep in mind when filing out your application.

1. The work has to include aspects of project management such as managing scope, schedule, budget, quality, risk, procurement, stakeholders, etc.
2. Make sure they way you describe your project experience is not too technical in detail that the person reviewing your application wouldn't understand your project management work experience.

3. Check the following exam content outline to get an idea of the types of tasks that would be acceptable for the application as well as the PMP Eligibility Requirements.

https://www.pmi.org/-/media/pmi/documents/public/pdf/certifications/pmp-examination-content-outline.pdf

column2: Can someone speak to why the resources available are for the PMBOK 6th edition when the 7th edition is what is being used for the exam?
column5:
The PMP ATP training uses the materials provided by PMI from their "PMI Authorized PMP Exam Prep", which we refer to in class as the Learner Kit. Their exam prep uses concepts from the Exam Content Outline. The outline is based on various publications (including PMBOK 6 and 7, and the Agile Practice Guide). 

Exam Content Outline:
https://www.pmi.org/-/media/pmi/documents/public/pdf/certifications/project-management-professional-exam-outline.pdf

column5:
The PMP ATP training uses the materials provided by PMI from their "PMI Authorized PMP Exam Prep", which we refer to in class as the Learner Kit. Their exam prep uses concepts from the Exam Content Outline. The outline is based on various publications (including PMBOK 6 and 7, and the Agile Practice Guide). 

Exam Content Outline:
https://www.pmi.org/-/media/pmi/documents/public/pdf/certifications/project-management-professional-exam-outline.pdf

Yes, please rewatch the video in your Bootcamp resources.

Percipio Users: Open a new tab in your browser first, and then follow the steps to find resources and then follow these steps.

Step 1. Log into Percipio
Step 2. Select Library > Showcase > Skillsoft Bootcamps
Step 3. Choose Project Management Bootcamps
Step 4. Select the Project Management Professional (PMP) ATP Bootcamp: 5 Day Cohort channel
Step 5. Select the Resources tab to the right of the Attend tab in the Bootcamp channel. Download the 5 Class Slides

Non-Percipio and Percipio users can access documents including the session slides and attendance tracker from GitHub.

https://github.com/Skillsoft-Content/PMP5Day

Click Code and then Download Zip to get all resources from GitHub.

column5: Please note that any session where you miss more than 15 minutes is considered a missed session. column2: Play music instead of answering questions 🤔
column5: We are answering questions during the breaks. Having music playing will not affect that

column2:
My advisors at IVMF Syracuse University replied that: "I appreciate the heads up for your upcoming appointments and that you won’t be able to attend the full sessions on those two days. We understand that appointments or travel come up and you are allowed to miss up to two sessions without being penalized and it will not impact your attendance or status for the bootcamp.

 

Please understand that they do mention at the start of the bootcamp that you cannot miss more than 15 minutes of a session however we do have an agreement with Skillsoft that allows learners to miss up to two sessions and still receive credit for attending the session.

 

We’ll be able to provide the recordings of that session as well so you can makeup anything that you may miss."

column2: How is attendance and thus certification of attendance provided to attendees?
column5:
Percipio should be tracking your attendance in each session if you are joining from Percipio. Your attendance is also being tracked by Zoom. At the end of the session, you will be able to upload a report from Percipio or your attendance tracking document when you request your certificate of completion. The request process will be covered in the last session, but you can review the video and documentation for attendance and the certificate of completion from the Project Management Professional (PMP) ATP Bootcamp: 5 Day Cohort channel in Percipio or from our GitHub site.

GitHub URL:
https://github.com/Skillsoft-Content/PMP5Day

column2: What is the difference between  CAPM vs PMP as I could see that the trainer says  CAPM ...
column5: What is the difference between  CAPM vs PMP as I could see that the trainer says  CAPM ...

column2: What is the difference between  CAPM vs PMP as I could see that the trainer says  CAPM ...
column5:
The CAPM is PMI's entry level certification, which is currently based directly on the content of the PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition. You can qualify for the CAPM simply by completing our CAPM courses. The PMP is a professional level certification intended for experienced project managers that requires attendees to have actual project experience. You can find details on each here:

https://www.pmi.org/certifications

column2: What is the last date to take the PMP exam based on this boot camp? current exam is based on pmbok6 and there will be a transition to pmbok7 exam?
column5: What is the last date to take the PMP exam based on this boot camp? current exam is based on pmbok6 and there will be a transition to pmbok7 exam?

column2: What is the last date to take the PMP exam based on this boot camp? current exam is based on pmbok6 and there will be a transition to pmbok7 exam?
column5:
Training hours for this Bootcamp does not expire. So you could take the exam in 2 years time if you want. The PMP ATP training uses the materials provided by PMI from their "PMI Authorized PMP Exam Prep", which we refer to in class as the Learner Kit. Their exam prep uses concepts from the Exam Content Outline. The outline is based on various publications (including PMBOK 6 and 7, and the Agile Practice Guide). 

Exam Content Outline:
https://www.pmi.org/-/media/pmi/documents/public/pdf/certifications/project-management-professional-exam-outline.pdf

column2: Signed in using Percipo...is there anyway to turn the chat off from having a pop up window?
column5: Signed in using Percipo...is there anyway to turn the chat off from having a pop up window?

column2: Signed in using Percipo...is there anyway to turn the chat off from having a pop up window?
column5:
If you are using the Zoom client click the upward facing carrot by that chat icon, click turn off chat previews

From the iPhone mobile app you can mute using these steps
1. Click the chat
2. Click the bell icon in the upper right hand corner
3. Select Mute

If you do not have the option to turn off previews or mute the chat, here are some suggestions to try:

- Open the chat window and push it off to the side and down, just leaving the title bar showing

column2: If the PM has the ability to enhance, update the IT Software, will that still be considered EEF or OPA now?
column5:
OPAs are any processes, knowledge, documents, or databases that your organization has created and developed or owns. OPAs can help in the planning of your project as well as for tailoring the organization's processes to fit the needs of the project.

EEFs can represent "anything" that is outside the control of the project team that can constrain, direct, or influence the project. External factors can also come from governments. EEFs impact the project by constraining or enhancing the project in a negative or positive way. Project management information system, which is a collection of software tools that help in the success of the project, is an EEF

column2: do companies try to predict inflation when calculating NPV or a historical reference
column5:
Companies typically try to predict future inflation when calculating NPV, as it is an important factor that can affect the value of cash flows over time. Inflation can affect the purchasing power of money, and if not taken into account, it can lead to an overestimation of the value of an investment.

When calculating NPV, companies will use a discount rate that takes into account the expected rate of inflation. This rate is typically the company's cost of capital, which includes the expected rate of return on the investment as well as the expected rate of inflation.

In practice, companies use a combination of both historical reference and prediction. they use historical inflation data to estimate a predicted inflation rate, which is then used in their NPV calculations. It's also common to use the expected inflation rate forecasted by the central bank or other independent economic institutions. Keep in mind that inflation predictions are uncertain, so the NPV calculations will also have a level of uncertainty

column2: Will you explain the PV vs NPV again - please?
column5: Will you explain the PV vs NPV again - please?

column2: Will you explain the PV vs NPV again - please?
column5:
PV (Present Value) and NPV (Net Present Value) are both financial metrics used to evaluate the profitability of a potential investment.

PV is a measure of the current value of an investment, taking into account the time value of money. It calculates the value of an investment at a certain point in time, typically the present, by discounting future cash flows using a discount rate.

NPV, on the other hand, is the difference between the present value of cash inflows and the present value of cash outflows of a project or investment. It is used to determine the profitability of an investment by considering all cash flows and the time value of money. A positive NPV indicates that an investment is profitable, while a negative NPV indicates that it is unprofitable.

Basically, PV is a single point in time calculation, while NPV is a cumulation of all cash flows over a period of time.

column2: how to verify/validate accuracy of the business value claimed in business case?
column5: how to verify/validate accuracy of the business value claimed in business case?

column2: how to verify/validate accuracy of the business value claimed in business case?
column5:
There are several methods to verify and validate the accuracy of the business value claimed in a business case. For instance:

Key Performance Indicator (KPI) tracking: Establish key performance indicators (KPIs) that align with the business value claimed in the business case and track them throughout the project. This allows you to measure the actual performance of the project and compare it to the projected performance in the business case.

Post-implementation review: Conduct a post-implementation review of the project to assess the actual business value achieved. This involves gathering feedback from stakeholders and analyzing project data to determine if the project met its objectives and delivered the expected business value.

Return on Investment (ROI) analysis: Use a ROI analysis to evaluate the financial performance of the project and compare it to the projected financial performance in the business case.

column5:
After a session is presented live, you can send a request to mentoring@skillsoft.com and we will give you a direct link to access the recording that is password protected or you can wait for the next session, and we can provide it for you then.

You can replace one live session with a recording and still qualify for the certificate of completion at the end of the bootcamp. If you miss more than one live session, you will need to attend the equivalent session in a future 5-Day Cohort. Please note that any session where you miss more than 15 minutes is considered a missed session.

column2: Percipio user - If we had to use Zoom because of Percipio audio issues, do we still need to use the tracker, or will our attendace still be tracked with the self-serve option? Thanks!
column5: IMPORTANT INFORMATION: Everyone should track their time in the attendance tracker. The attendance tracker is needed when using the certificate request process to get your certificate. If for some reason your attendance isn't perfect and you cant get your certificate using the self-serve option, which is only available to Percipio users, then you will need to use the certificate request process to get your certificate. column2: Is there a connection between Project Governance and Compliance?

Governance is the framework, functions, and processes that guide project management activities to create a unique product, service, or result to meet organizational, strategic, and operational goals.​

Compliance are basically Legal or regulatory constraints.
